There is no analogue to the OPACUserCSS preference in the staff
        client, but you can get around this by putting this in the intranetuserjs preference:
        //]]>
</script>
<style type="text/css">
 /* inline styles */
 </style>
<script type="text/javascript">
//<![CDATA[

In the above snippet where it says /* inline styles */ we'll
        redeclare the relevant properties from the styles of the login
        image://]]>
</script>
